Start simple using this code to just run the elevator up and down.

public class Elevator extends SubsystemBase { private final SparkFlex elevatorMotor = new SparkFlex(11, MotorType.kBrushless); public final RelativeEncoder elevatorEncoder = elevatorMotor.getEncoder();

}

Then in Robot Container add this

controleXbox.rightTrigger.whileHeld((elevatorSubsystem.runElevator(.5)) .onFalse(elevatorSubsystem.stopElevator());

controleXbox.leftTrigger.whileHeld((elevatorSubsystem.runElevator(-.5)) .onFalse(elevatorSubsystem.stopElevator());

These should let you run the elevator up and down at 1/2 speed. Make sure Shuffleboard is showing the elevator position and speed Move the elevator 1 meter and note how much elevator position reading changes. This will be the number of motor turns it takes to move the elevator 1 meter. You can check this number with the mechanics of the elevator. We can go further when you have this number.
